communications/campaigns/beta_campaign/icons/icon_03.png</ThumbnailImage><xPower Type="GroupStart" GroupStart="" Name="IntroText" label="Intro Text" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Expanded="true"><IntroCopy type="dhtml" label="Intro Text" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<p>There's no question the Internet is a powerful way to communicate.  And at BYU-Idaho, we have a wonderful story to tell. Following the  Church's <a href="http://lds.org/church/news/church-members-share-the-gospel-online?lang=eng" title="Church News article about initiative to increase positive LDS information online.">example</a> of positive online communication, BYU-Idaho recently launched official pages on <a href="http://www.facebook.com/pages/BYU-Idaho/140492225964954" title="Official BYU-Idaho Facebook Page">Facebook</a> and <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/byui" title="Official BYU-Idaho YouTube Channel">YouTube</a>,  with plans to include LinkedIn, Twitter, and others. The new site  provides convenient "like" links on news articles that can post to over  300 social networking sites and even personal blogs.</p>
